<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">Install CDF and Suite</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 4 minutes to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>To install ITOM Container Foundation (CDF) on the master node, follow these steps:
</p><p><b>Note</b>: In the following Container Deployment Foundation  installation steps, the temporary directory  <code>ITOM_Suite_Foundation_2019.05.00xxx</code> will be referred to as  <code>&lt;foundation_temp_dir&gt;</code> . 
</p>
<ol>
<li>Run the following command to navigate to the CDF installation directory:
<p class="mw-empty-elt"></p><pre>cd &lt;foundation_temp_dir&gt;</pre><p class="mw-empty-elt"></p></li>
<li>Run one of the following commands:
<p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p><a class="buttonfullscr" onclick="javascript:loadingTableButton(this);"><button class="flscrbtn"><i class="material-icons flscricn">open_in_new</i><div style="margin: auto 5px;">View Fullscreen</div></button></a><table>
<tbody><tr>
<th>Condition
</th>
<th>Command
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>If you are the root user
</td>
<td><b>./install -m /&lt;Product_metadata_directory&gt;/&lt;product_metadata&gt;.tgz [Options]</b>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>If you are a sudo user
</td>
<td><b>sudo ./install -m /&lt;Product_metadata_directory&gt;/&lt;product_metadata&gt;.tgz [Options]</b>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>If you want to skip the warnings during the installation
</td>
<td><b>sudo ./install -m --skip-warning /&lt;Product_metadata_directory&gt;/&lt;product_metadata&gt;.tgz [Options]</b>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<p class="mw-empty-elt"></p>
Enter the administrator's password and wait until the installation on the first master node is complete.<br>You can specify the following options to configure the Kubernetes cluster:<p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p><a class="buttonfullscr" onclick="javascript:loadingTableButton(this);"><button class="flscrbtn"><i class="material-icons flscricn">open_in_new</i><div style="margin: auto 5px;">View Fullscreen</div></button></a><table>

<tbody><tr>
<th>Options
</th>
<th>Description
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>registry-orgname
</td>
<td>Specifies the organization name (lower-case) where the suite images are placed. The default organization name is hpeswitom.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>docker-http-proxy
</td>
<td>Specifies the proxy settings for Docker. Configure this parameter if access to the Docker hub or registry requires a proxy (by default, no proxy is used).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>docker-https-proxy
</td>
<td>Specifies the proxy settings for Docker. Configure this parameter if access to the Docker hub or registry requires a proxy (by default, no proxy is used).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>docker-no-proxy
</td>
<td>Specifies the IPv4 address or FQDN that does not need proxy settings for Docker.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>flannel-backend-type
</td>
<td>Specifies the backend type of the flannel network. The allowable values of this parameter are: host-gw and vxlan. By default, host-gw is used.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>flannel-iface
</td>
<td>Specifies the interface for Docker inter-host communication as a single IPv4 address or interface name. This parameter is used when the nodes have more than one network adapter.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>k8s-home
</td>
<td>Specifies the absolute path of the installation directory for the CDF binaries. By default, the CDF installation directory is /opt/kubernetes.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>keepalived-nopreempt
</td>
<td>Specifies whether to enable nopreempt mode for KeepAlived. The allowable value of this parameter is true or false. By default, the value is 'true' and KeepAlived is started in nopreempt mode.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>keepalived-virtual-router-id
</td>
<td>Virtual router id should be unique for each cluster in the same network segment. But all nodes in the same cluster should use the same value. The value should be between 0 and 255.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>pod-cidr
</td>
<td>Specifies the network address for pods with CIDR notation. Allowable format is: x.x.0.0/16. Default value is 172.16.0.0/16.
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p class="mw-empty-elt"></p></li></ol><p>If your system is behind a firewall, ensure that you provide the <code>docker-http-proxy</code>, <code>docker-https-proxy</code> and <code>docker-no-proxy</code> parameters in the command.
</p><p>For example,
</p>
<pre>./install -m /tmp/&lt;&lt;product_metadata_directory&gt;/&lt;product_metadata&gt;.tgz&gt; --docker-http-proxy http://yourproxyserver.yourdomain.com:proxy_port --docker-https-proxy http://yourproxyserver.yourdomain.com:proxy_port --docker-no-proxy localhost.yourdomain.com,127.0.0.1
</pre>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="View_the_installation_log">View the installation log</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/ICDFSuOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: View the installation log">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/ICDFSuOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: View the installation log">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>To view the installation log, run the <code>vi  /opt/kubernetes/log/scripts/install/install.&lt;timestamp&gt;.log</code> command.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Log_on_to_the_installation_portal">Log on to the installation portal</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/ICDFSuOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=2" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Log on to the installation portal">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/ICDFSuOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Log on to the installation portal">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>After you install CDF you will be provided with a URL using which you can access the installation portal.   
To log on to the installation portal:
</p>
<ol>
<li>Copy the installation portal URL provided at the end of the <b>Install CDF</b> step to a supported browser. The URL uses the format: <b>https://&lt;host&gt;:3000.</b></li>
<li>Log on to the installation portal with the suite administrator credentials that you provided while executing the <b>./install</b> command:</li>
<ul><li>Username: admin</li>
<li>Password: the password you provided</li></ul>
<li>Click <b>LOGIN</b>.</li>
If you exit the installation portal at any point, the installation process is stalled. The next time you log on to the portal, the installation process resumes from the point where you had stopped earlier.</ol>

